<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T006 Digital Setup Packet</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.45;color:#111827}h1{color:#0f172a}h2{border-bottom:1px solid #cbd5e1}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:12px 0}td,th{border:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding:8px}th{background:#e2e8f0}.note{background:#f8fafc;border-left:5px solid #0ea5e9;padding:10px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Digital Setup Packet</h1><p><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T006<br><b>Scenario:</b> Services, photos, and messages to one request path</p><p><img src="../assets/sample-digital-setup-proof.svg" style="width:100%;max-width:760px"></p><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Service descriptions, coverage area, photos, and current contact method.</li><li>Problem: customers ask questions in too many places and details get missed.</li><li>Goal: one clean path from page to form to tracker to reply.</li></ul><h2>Setup map</h2><table><tr><th>Step</th><th>Built output</th><th>Customer result</th></tr><tr><td>Page</td><td>Headline, service sections, proof, FAQ, CTA.</td><td>Visitor understands what to request.</td></tr><tr><td>Form</td><td>Fields for service, goal, files, timing, budget.</td><td>Owner gets usable info first time.</td></tr><tr><td>Tracker</td><td>Status, next action, due date, package, amount.</td><td>No request gets lost.</td></tr><tr><td>Reply</td><td>Confirmation and missing-info templates.</td><td>Faster first response.</td></tr></table><h2>Recommended first build</h2><div class="note">Start with one page, one request form, one lead tracker, and two email templates before adding more tools.</div></body></html>